From dc771142c1e255758b38c988c3cf0148199afde1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 13:30:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add 15pc slab, free per-package letter topper,
 per-product-per-package stock

Three features (PR #2/#4 scope) plus full wiring end-to-end:

1. Slab sizing - new slab-15 package alongside slab-12. Admin gets two
   independent per-size toggles (is_slab_available, is_slab_15_available).

2. Letter topper reworked from a paid LKR-350 addon to a free, built-in
   option. Limit is now per-package (packages.letter_max_chars): 7 chars/line
   for both slab sizes, 5 for the 15pc box, 4 for the 12pc box, not offered
   for the 9pc box. The old letter_topper addon row is kept (price 0,
   disabled) only so historical orders still render.

3. Per-product-per-package stock (product_package_stock table) - any
   product x package combo can be individually marked sold out (no row = in
   stock). Out-of-stock combos show disabled/struck-through in the storefront
   package selector rather than disappearing.

Wired through migration -> setup.sql -> seed-data.ts -> snapshot.ts ->
liveCatalog.ts (the runtime fetch path added by live-catalog-reads) ->
types/catalog.ts -> ProductConfigurator/PackageSelector/AddonPanel ->
admin ProductFormModal/Products page + new admin hooks.

Migration 013_slab_stock_letters.sql was written fresh this session - it
did not actually exist on claude/live-catalog-reads as referenced; checked
full repo history, no trace on any branch.

Branched off claude/live-catalog-reads (PR #3, open/not yet merged) since
this depends on the live-catalog fetch plumbing it added.

Verified: tsc -b clean, npm test 60/60 (59 baseline + 1 addon test split
for per-package limits), npm run lint 0 errors, npm run build (client + SSR
+ prerender) succeeds. Spot-checked prerendered HTML for dual-slab filtering
and out-of-stock rendering.

HANDOFF.md and GOLDEN_OVEN_BUILD_SPEC.md updated to match.
